('JAVA', 'Medium', 'What is the difference between checked and unchecked exceptions in Java? (Refresher)', 'There is no difference', 'Unchecked exceptions are more serious', 'Checked exceptions occur at runtime; unchecked at compile time', 'Checked exceptions must be caught or declared (compile-time); unchecked exceptions don''t require explicit handling (runtime)', 'D', 'Checked exceptions (IOException, SQLException) must be caught or declared in the method signature. Unchecked exceptions (NullPointerException, ArithmeticException) extend RuntimeException and don''t require explicit handling.', 'exceptions,checked-unchecked'),
('JAVA', 'Hard', 'For interview purposes: What is a lambda expression in Java? (Practice)', 'A design pattern for database access', 'A concise way to represent an anonymous function that implements a functional interface', 'A type of loop', 'A new data type', 'B', 'Lambda expressions (Java 8+) provide a concise syntax for implementing functional interfaces (interfaces with one abstract method). Example: (a, b) -> a + b. They enable functional programming in Java.', 'lambda,functional,java8'),
