('JAVA', 'Medium', 'In typical scenarios, What is a Java interface? (Variant)', 'A type of variable', 'A design pattern', 'A class that can be instantiated', 'A contract that defines methods a class must implement', 'D', 'An interface defines a contract of abstract methods that implementing classes must provide. Since Java 8, interfaces can also have default and static methods. A class can implement multiple interfaces.', 'interface,oop'),
('JAVA', 'Easy', 'Consider this: What is method overloading in Java? (Variant)', 'Calling a method recursively', 'Defining multiple methods with the same name but different parameter lists in the same class', 'Making a method static', 'Redefining a parent class method in a child class', 'B', 'Method overloading allows multiple methods with the same name but different parameter types, counts, or order. The compiler determines which version to call based on the arguments provided.', 'overloading,oop'),
