('PYTHON', 'Hard', 'Review concept: What is a metaclass in Python? (Practice)', 'A private class', 'A static class', 'A class that inherits from multiple parents', 'A class whose instances are classes themselves — it defines how classes are created', 'D', 'A metaclass is the ''class of a class.'' Just as a class defines how instances behave, a metaclass defines how classes behave. The default metaclass is ''type''. Metaclasses are used for frameworks and ORMs.', 'metaclass,advanced,oop'),
